(1) Implementation of epidural analgesia for labor to all patients;

This is one of the four standards measured during the audit cycle. The text states that "During the audit period epidural analgesia increased from 15.5% of all labors in the first trimester of the study to 51% in the last trimester (p<0.005)." This suggests that the standard of implementing epidural analgesia for labor was not initially reached by all women, but it did increase over time.
